But it gives me cause for a shout-out to *Unfamiliar Fishes*, by the hilarious yet trenchant Sarah Vowell. Vowell uses a Hawaiian Plate Lunch--similar to a Poke Bowl, with its fusion of Asian and European cuisines--as a springboard for a history of the 19th c. American colonization of Hawaii.

@Bill 

