Well, since we crossworders are expected to know some basic vocabulary in French, Spanish, Italian, and German, it's only fair that we should be quizzed on Russian, Japanese, and Chinese as well. (Not that I do so well on those.) My only quibble with SAN is that any Latin transliteration of Chinese only preserves some of the pronunciation--it ignores the tones, without which the words are ambiguous.

I was trying to put some pumice into my exfoliant--LAVA, perhaps? TALC was too soft, and GRIT was too generic.

